<span><br></span><span><br></span></strong></span><span>      <ul><span><li><!---->Competitive Compensation (base + bonus &amp; equity)<!----></li></span><span><li><!---->Comprehensive medical, dental, and vision coverage with Health Savings Account contributions from Upstart<span class="white-space-pre"> </span></li></span><span><li><!---->401(k) with 100% company match up to $4,500 and immediate vesting and after-tax savings<!----></li></span><span><li><!---->Employee Stock Purchase Plan (ESPP)<!----></li></span><span><li><!---->Life and disability insurance<!----></li></span><span><li><!---->Generous holiday, vacation, sick and safety leave<span class="white-space-pre"> </span></li></span><span><li><!---->Supportive parental, family care, and military leave programs<!----></li></span><span><li><!---->Annual wellness, technology &amp; ergonomic reimbursement programs<!----></li></span><span><li><!---->Social activities including team events and onsites, all-company updates, employee resource groups (ERGs), and other interest groups such as book clubs, fitness, investing, and volunteering<!----></li></span><span><li><!---->Catered lunches + snacks &amp; drinks when working in offices<!----><span><br></span><span><br></span></li></span></ul>\n</span><!---->At Upstart, your base pay is one part of your total compensation package. The anticipated base salary for this position is expected to be within the below range. Your actual base pay will depend on your geographic location–with our “digital first” philosophy, Upstart uses compensation regions that vary depending on location. Individual pay is also determined by job-related skills, experience, and relevant education or training. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for your preferred location during the hiring process.<!----><span><br></span><span><br></span><!---->In addition, Upstart provides employees with target bonuses, equity compensation, and generous benefits packages (including medical, dental, vision, and 401k).<!----><span><br></span><span><br></span><!---->United States | Remote - Anticipated Base Salary Range<!----><span><br></span><span><br></span><!---->$142,000—$196,600 USD<!----><span><br></span><span><br></span><!---->Upstart is a proud Equal Opportunity Employer. We are dedicated to ensuring that underrepresented classes receive better access to affordable credit, and are just as committed to embracing diversity and inclusion in our hiring practices. We celebrate all cultures, backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences, and know that we can only become better together.<!----><span><br></span><span><br></span><span><em><!---->If you require reasonable accommodation in completing an application, interviewing, completing any pre-employment testing, or otherwise participating in the employee selection process, please email<span class="white-space-pre"> </span></em></span><span><em><!---->candidate_accommodations@upstart.com<!----><span><br></span><span><br></span></em></span><a class="qcgcnyuktFtlrNjpAvprsXbFKLHNVBeXAarvGqTg " target="_blank" tabindex="0" href="https://www.upstart.com/candidate_privacy_policy" data-test-app-aware-link=""><!---->https://www.upstart.com/candidate_privacy_policy<!----><span><br></span><span><br></span></a>\n                </p>\n<!---->            </div>\n          </div>\n          <div class="jobs-description__details">\n<!---->          </div>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n<!---->    </div>', 'employment_type': None, 'error_log': 'Filler completed with non-success status: application_failed_ats', 'is_remote': True, 'job_details_pdf_path': '/Users/vipul/Desktop/Project/job_agent/output_documents/Upstart_Software_Engineer_Consumer_Platform_with_verificat_681be089c99e3b44d697f2a0/Job_Details_Report.pdf', 'job_specific_output_dir': '/Users/vipul/Desktop/Project/job_agent/output_documents/Upstart_Software_Engineer_Consumer_Platform_with_verificat_681be089c99e3b44d697f2a0', 'job_summary': None, 'job_title': 'Software Engineer, Consumer Platform with verification', 'last_updated': datetime.datetime(2025, 5, 9, 1, 1, 53, 261000), 'location': 'United States (Remote)', 'personal_social_connections': None, 'publish_time': '2025-05-07', 'publish_time_desc': '2 hours ago', 'qualifications': None, 'resume_pdf_path': '/Users/vipul/Desktop/Project/job_agent/output_documents/Upstart_Software_Engineer_Consumer_Platform_with_verificat_681be089c99e3b44d697f2a0/Resume.pdf', 'seniority_level': None, 'skills': None, 'social_connections': None, 'source_job_id': '4223058960', 'source_platform': 'linkedin', 'source_url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4223058960/?eBP=NON_CHARGEABLE_CHANNEL&refId=4H9aXGUniDj1aGV02FlUEA%3D%3D&trackingId=FAv22AnqQcoUQfL1p6C8aw%3D%3D&trk=flagship3_search_srp_jobs', 'sources_list': ['linkedin'], 'status': 'docs_ready', 'status_reason': 'Docs generated in Upstart_Software_Engineer_Consumer_Platform_with_verificat_681be089c99e3b44d697f2a0', 'tailored_cover_letter_text': "\\documentclass[letterpaper,11pt]{article}\n\n\\usepackage[english]{babel}\n\\usepackage[utf8]{inputenc} % Keep inputenc for handling source file encoding\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage[hidelinks]{hyperref} % Keep hidelinks if you prefer no boxes\n\\usepackage{geometry} % For adjusting margins\n\\usepackage{parskip} % Adds space between paragraphs instead of indentation\n\\usepackage{xurl} % Add xurl for better link/path breaking if needed\n\n% Adjust margins (similar to resume, or adjust as needed for letter format)\n\\geometry{\n  letterpaper,\n  left=1in,\n  right=1in,\n  top=1in,\n  bottom=1in\n}\n\n\\urlstyle{same} % Use current text font for URLs\n\\pagestyle{empty} % No page numbers for a cover letter\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n% --- Your Contact Information ---\n\\begin{raggedright} % Keep your info left-aligned\n\\textbf{\\Large Bhupesh Chikara} \\\\ % <<< Placeholder for your name\n% Optional: Add address if needed, but phone/email/linkedin are often sufficient\n% [YOUR_ADDRESS] \\\\ % Uncomment if needed\n% [YOUR_CITY_STATE_ZIP] \\\\ % Uncomment if needed\n+1-3155757385 \\\\ % <<< Placeholder\n\\href{mailto:bchikara@syr.edu}{\\nolinkurl{bchikara@syr.edu}} \\\\ % <<< Placeholder\n\\href{https://www.linkedin.com/in/bchikara/}{\\nolinkurl{linkedin.com/in/bchikara/}} \\\\ % <<< Placeholder\n\\href{}{\\nolinkurl{}} % <<< Placeholder\n\\vspace{2\\baselineskip} % Add space before date\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n% --- Date ---\n\\begin{raggedright}\n\\today \\\\ % Automatically inserts the current date\n\\vspace{2\\baselineskip} % Add space before recipient info\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n% --- Recipient Information ---\n% Placeholders will be replaced by tailor.py with escaped content\n\\begin{raggedright}\nHiring Team\n\nUpstart\n[Company Address]\nUnited States (Remote)\n\\vspace{2\\baselineskip} % Add space before salutation\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n% --- Salutation ---\n% Placeholder will be replaced by tailor.py with escaped content\n\\begin{raggedright}\nDear Dear Hiring Team, \\\\\n\\vspace{1\\baselineskip} % Add space before body\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n% --- Body Paragraph 1: Introduction ---\n% <<< Use unique, static placeholder >>>\n\\begin{raggedright}\nI am writing to express my enthusiastic interest in the Software Engineer, Consumer Platform with verification position at Upstart, as seen on LinkedIn.  Upstart's mission of expanding access to affordable credit through AI-driven lending deeply resonates with me, and the opportunity to contribute to such an innovative and impactful company is incredibly exciting. My extensive experience in full-stack development, particularly with React and backend technologies like Kotlin and Ruby, aligns perfectly with the technical requirements outlined in the job description.\n\\vspace{1\\baselineskip}\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n% --- Body Paragraph 2: Qualifications Match ---\n% <<< Use unique, static placeholder >>>\n\\begin{raggedright}\nMy background includes three consecutive Applause Awards at Deloitte, recognizing my contributions to team leadership, project ownership, and solving complex dashboard algorithms using React and Next.js---skills directly applicable to designing and developing resilient services for Upstart's consumer platform.  Furthermore, my experience at ToTheNew Pvt. Ltd., where I developed front-end solutions for e-commerce platforms using Angular, demonstrates my ability to build reusable components and maintainable solutions, fulfilling a key preferred qualification.  Finally, winning a state-level hackathon for a project connecting NGOs and food beneficiaries showcases my problem-solving abilities and commitment to impactful projects, aligning with Upstart's focus on improving consumer experiences.\n\\vspace{1\\baselineskip}\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n% --- Body Paragraph 3: Why This Company/Role ---\n% <<< Use unique, static placeholder >>>\n\\begin{raggedright}\nUpstart's commitment to leveraging AI for positive social impact, coupled with its innovative approach to lending, is particularly appealing. The opportunity to work on a core product platform, collaborating with cross-functional teams to create scalable and seamless consumer experiences, perfectly aligns with my career aspirations. I am confident that my skills and experience would be a valuable asset to your team, and I am eager to discuss how I can contribute to Upstart's continued success. Thank you for your time and consideration.\n\\vspace{1\\baselineskip}\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n% --- Closing Paragraph ---\n% Placeholder will be replaced by tailor.py with escaped content\n\\begin{raggedright}\nThank you for considering my application. I have attached my resume for your review and welcome the opportunity to discuss how my skills and experience can benefit Upstart in an interview.\n\\vspace{2\\baselineskip} % Add space before closing\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n% --- Closing ---\n\\begin{raggedright}\nSincerely, \\\\\n\\vspace{3\\baselineskip} % Leave space for signature (optional for digital)\nBhupesh Chikara % <<< Placeholder for your name\n\\end{raggedright}\n\n\\end{document}\n", 'tailored_resume_text': '%-------------------------\n% Resume in Latex\n% Author : Jake Gutierrez / Modifications for Job Agent\n% Based off of: https://github.com/sb2nov/resume\n% License : MIT\n%------------------------\n\n\\documentclass[letterpaper,11pt]{article}\n\n\\usepackage{latexsym}\n\\usepackage[empty]{fullpage}\n\\usepackage{titlesec}\n\\usepackage{marvosym}\n\\usepackage[usenames,dvipsnames]{color}\n\\usepackage{verbatim}\n\\usepackage{enumitem}\n\\usepackage[hidelinks]{hyperref} % Keep hidelinks if you prefer no boxes around links\n\\usepackage{fancyhdr}\n\\usepackage[english]{babel}\n\\usepackage{tabularx}\n\\usepackage{xurl} % <<< For better line breaking\n% \\usepackage{fontawesome5} % Uncomment if you want to use icons in the header\n\\input{glyphtounicode}\n\n%----------FONT OPTIONS----------\n% sans-serif\n% \\usepackage[sfdefault]{FiraSans}\n% \\usepackage[sfdefault]{roboto}\n% \\usepackage[sfdefault]{noto-sans}\n% \\usepackage[default]{sourcesanspro} % A good, clean sans-serif option\n\n% serif\n% \\usepackage{CormorantGaramond}\n% \\usepackage{charter} % A good serif option\n\n\n\\pagestyle{fancy}\n\\fancyhf{} % clear all header and footer fields\n\\fancyfoot{}\n\\renewcommand{\\headrulewidth}{0pt}\n\\renewcommand{\\footrulewidth}{0pt}\n\n% Adjust margins\n\\addtolength{\\oddsidemargin}{-0.5in}\n\\addtolength{\\evensidemargin}{-0.5in}\n\\addtolength{\\textwidth}{1in}\n\\addtolength{\\topmargin}{-.5in}\n\\addtolength{\\textheight}{1.0in}\n\n% Set URL style - \\urlstyle{same} uses the current text font\n\\urlstyle{same}\n\n\\raggedbottom\n\\raggedright\n\\setlength{\\tabcolsep}{0in}\n\n% Sections formatting\n\\titleformat{\\section}{\n  \\vspace{-4pt}\\scshape\\raggedright\\large\n}{}{0em}{}[\\color{black}\\titlerule \\vspace{-5pt}]\n\n% Ensure that generated pdf is machine readable/ATS parsable\n\\pdfgentounicode=1\n\n%-------------------------\n% Custom commands (Keep these as they define the resume structure)\n\\newcommand{\\resumeItem}[1]{\n  \\item\\small{\n    {#1 \\vspace{-2pt}}\n  }\n}\n\n\\newcommand{\\resumeSubheading}[4]{\n  \\vspace{-2pt}\\item\n    \\begin{tabular*}{0.97\\textwidth}[t]{l@{\\extracolsep{\\fill}}r}\n      \\textbf{#1} & #2 \\\\\n      \\textit{\\small#3} & \\textit{\\small #4} \\\\\n    \\end{tabular*}\\vspace{-7pt}\n}\n\n\\newcommand{\\resumeSubSubheading}[2]{\n    \\item\n    \\begin{tabular*}{0.97\\textwidth}{l@{\\extracolsep{\\fill}}r}\n      \\textit{\\small#1} & \\textit{\\small #2} \\\\\n    \\end{tabular*}\\vspace{-7pt}\n}\n\n\\newcommand{\\resumeProjectHeading}[2]{\n    \\item\n    \\begin{tabular*}{0.97\\textwidth}{l@{\\extracolsep{\\fill}}r}\n      \\small\\textbf{#1} & #2 \\\\\n    \\end{tabular*}\\vspace{-7pt}\n}\n\n\\newcommand{\\resumeSubItem}[1]{\\resumeItem{#1}\\vspace{-4pt}}\n\n\\renewcommand\\labelitemii{$\\vcenter{\\hbox{\\tiny$\\bullet$}}$}\n\n\\newcommand{\\resumeSubHeadingListStart}{\\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=0.15in, label={}]}\n\\newcommand{\\resumeSubHeadingListEnd}{\\end{itemize}}\n\\newcommand{\\resumeItemListStart}{\\begin{itemize}}\n\\newcommand{\\resumeItemListEnd}{\\end{itemize}\\vspace{-5pt}}\n\n%-------------------------------------------\n%%%%%%  RESUME STARTS HERE  %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%\n\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n\n%----------HEADING----------\n% Ensure this matches your desired header format\n% Replace placeholders with actual data from config or candidate profile\n\\begin{center}\n    \\textbf{\\Huge \\scshape Bhupesh Chikara} \\\\ \\vspace{1pt}\n    \\small +1-3155757385 $|$\n    \\href{mailto:bchikara@syr.edu}{\\nolinkurl{bchikara@syr.edu}} $|$\n    \\href{https://www.linkedin.com/in/bchikara/}{\\nolinkurl{linkedin.com/in/bchikara/}} $|$\n    \\href{None}{\\nolinkurl{}}\n    \n\\end{center}\n\n\n%-----------EDUCATION-----------\n\\section{Education}\n  \\resumeSubHeadingListStart\n    \\resumeSubheading\n      {Syracuse University}{Syracuse, NY}\n      {Master of Science in Computer Science}{Jan 2024 -- Dec 2025}\n    \\resumeSubheading\n      {DIT University}{Dehradun, India}\n      {Bachelor of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering}{Aug 2016 -- May 2020}\n  \\resumeSubHeadingListEnd\n\n\n%-----------EXPERIENCE-----------\n\\section{Experience}\n  \\resumeSubHeadingListStart\n\n\\resumeSubheading{\\textbf{Deloitte} $|$ \\emph{Senior Software Engineer}}{Feb 2021 -- Jan 2024}{React, Next.js, TypeScript, Node.js, Redux, AWS, D3.js, Three.js}{Bangalore, India}\n  \\resumeItemListStart\n    \\resumeItem{Developed and implemented responsive dashboards and fragments for Deloitte Insights using React, Next.js, and Redux, resulting in a 35\\% increase in user engagement and improved data visualization.}\n    \\resumeItem{Utilized D3.js to create interactive charts and graphs for real-time data exploration, reducing decision-making time by 25\\% and enhancing data accuracy.}\n    \\resumeItem{Leveraged Three.js to build 3D data visualizations, improving user experience and data accuracy by 20\\%, showcasing a strong understanding of data representation.}\n    \\resumeItem{Spearheaded cross-functional collaboration to design, deploy, and maintain 3 new systems, increasing team efficiency and expanding tool utilization across 15+ departments, demonstrating project ownership and leadership skills.}\n  \\resumeItemListEnd\n\n\\resumeSubheading{\\textbf{ToTheNew Pvt. Ltd.} $|$ \\emph{Software Engineer}}{Feb 2020 -- Mar 2021}{Angular 4+, Node.js, RxJS, MongoDB, Express}{Noida, India}\n  \\resumeItemListStart\n    \\resumeItem{Developed front-end solutions, including a COVID-19 dashboard and e-commerce platforms, using Angular 4+, RxJS, and REST APIs, exceeding client expectations for PWC.}\n    \\resumeItem{Architected and implemented the TCH channel studying portal using Angular 4+, REST APIs, and RxJS, enhancing user experience and knowledge retention.}\n    \\resumeItem{Improved application performance by 50\\% by implementing RxJS for asynchronous task handling, resulting in a 15\\% increase in user retention rates, showcasing expertise in optimizing application performance.}\n  \\resumeItemListEnd\n\n\\resumeSubheading{\\textbf{Smart Joules Pvt. Ltd.} $|$ \\emph{Joule Fellow}}{Sept 2018 -- Dec 2019}{Angular, D3.js, TypeScript, RxJS}{Dehradun, India}\n  \\resumeItemListStart\n    \\resumeItem{Built several applications, including D3 dashboards and a multi-select autocomplete component, within the Smart Joules track system, demonstrating proficiency in front-end development.}\n    \\resumeItem{Developed and open-sourced an NPM module for multi-select autocomplete, fostering code reusability and collaboration, leading to a 40\\% increase in community contributions, showcasing initiative and problem-solving skills.}\n    \\resumeItem{Created interactive D3 dashboards using Angular and RxJS, enhancing application functionality and responsiveness, demonstrating skills in data visualization and front-end frameworks.}\n  \\resumeItemListEnd\n\n  \\resumeSubHeadingListEnd\n\n\n%-----------PROJECTS-----------\n\\section{Projects}\n    \\resumeSubHeadingListStart\n\n\\resumeProjectHeading{\\textbf{ScanFeast Mobile Web App} $|$ \\emph{React, Redux, D3.js, Firebase, Next.js}}{Aug 2024 -- Present}\n  \\resumeItemListStart\n    \\resumeItem{Developed a React and Redux-based restaurant application enabling seamless order placement via QR code scanning, improving order processing efficiency by 20\\%.}\n    \\resumeItem{Integrated Firebase for optimized backend operations, enhancing data storage and retrieval speed by 30\\%, ensuring data accuracy and freshness.}\n    \\resumeItem{Created interactive charts and graphs using D3.js for the restaurant dashboard, providing valuable insights for efficient order management, demonstrating data visualization skills.}\n  \\resumeItemListEnd\n\n\\resumeProjectHeading{\\textbf{MedConnect Mobile Web App} $|$ \\emph{React, Redux, Node.js, MongoDB, AWS, TypeScript, Next.js}}{Sept 2024 -- Present}\n  \\resumeItemListStart\n    \\resumeItem{Engineered a full-stack mobile web application using Node.js for backend REST API services and React for frontend interactions, supporting over 500 weekly active users.}\n    \\resumeItem{Implemented JWT authentication to enhance data security protocols by 40\\%, ensuring secure data retrieval and user privacy.}\n    \\resumeItem{Developed a search interface using Algolia search, reducing search times by 25\\% and improving the overall user experience, demonstrating problem-solving skills.}\n  \\resumeItemListEnd\n\n    \\resumeSubHeadingListEnd\n\n\n%-----------TECHNICAL SKILLS-----------\n\\section{Technical Skills}\n \\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=0.15in, itemsep=1pt, topsep=2pt, parsep=0pt, label={}]\n\n    \\item \\small \\textbf{Skills:} React, Next.js, Redux, RxJS, Node.js, TypeScript, JavaScript, HTML/CSS, D3.js, AWS, Kotlin, Ruby, SQL, API Design, Microservices, Data Structures and Algorithms, System Design, Agile, Testing.\n    \\item \\small \\textbf{Tools:} Git, Firebase, Docker, AWS, MongoDB, Algolia, Selenium automation.\n\n \\end{itemize}\n\n\n%-------------------------------------------\n\\end{document}\n', 'work_model': 'Remote', 'last_attempted_at': datetime.datetime(2025, 5, 9, 0, 43, 48, 358000)}. Problematic raw user_profile (first 200 chars): {'full_name': 'Bhupesh Chikara', 'email': 'bchikara@syr.edu', 'phone': '+1-3155757385', 'linkedin': 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/bchikara/', 'github': None, 'website': 'bchikara.com', 'first_name': 'Bhupesh', 'last_name': 'Chikara', 'location': 'New York'}
